verses.verse: A Song<WH7892> of degrees<WH4609>. Unto thee lift I up<WH5375> mine eyes<WH5869>, O thou that dwellest<WH3427> in the heavens<WH8064>.

Behold, as the eyes<WH5869> of servants<WH5650> look unto the hand<WH3027> of their masters<WH113>, and as the eyes<WH5869> of a maiden<WH8198> unto the hand<WH3027> of her mistress<WH1404>; so our eyes<WH5869> wait upon the LORD<WH3068> our God<WH430>, until that he have mercy<WH2603> upon us.
Have mercy<WH2603> upon us, O LORD<WH3068>, have mercy<WH2603> upon us: for we are exceedingly<WH7227> filled<WH7646> with contempt<WH937>.
Our soul<WH5315> is exceedingly<WH7227> filled<WH7646> with the scorning<WH3933> of those that are at ease<WH7600>, and with the contempt<WH937> of the proud<WH3238> <WH1343> <WH1349>.
